  "abstract": {
    "value": "CuI-catalyzed decarboxylative phosphonylation of terminal alkyne-substituted cyclic carbonates/carbamates with phosphine oxides has been developed relying on the highly regioselective addition at the α-position of the in situ generated copper-allenylidene intermediates. A series of 4-phosphonyl 2,3-allenols and 4-phosphonyl 2,3-allenamines were smoothly obtained in moderate to excellent yields under mild conditions. The synthetic utility of this methodology was demonstrated by large-scale synthesis and versatile transformations of the products.",
